cs.DS, cs.CG, cs.DM, cs.GT, cs.AI. 

The paper deals with scheduling and optimization problems related to covering a region with sensors, which involves concepts from computational geometry (such as rectangles in space and time) and algorithms (such as approximation algorithms). Therefore, the most likely category is cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), followed by cs.CG (Computational Geometry) and cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics). The problem also involves optimization and game theory concepts, which could place it in categories such as cs.GT (Game Theory) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence).
